- Open cmd or powershell console
- Type "netdom query fsmo" without quotes to verify all roles on dc 
C:\Users\Administrator.RECTOVERSO>netdom query fsmo
Schema master               ad-1.rectoverso.com
Domain naming master        ad-1.rectoverso.com
PDC                         ad-1.rectoverso.com
RID pool manager            ad-1.rectoverso.com
Infrastructure master       ad-1.rectoverso.com
The command completed successfully.

- Type "ntdsutil" then enter -- follow the instructions below -- in here i want to transfer RID pool manager from ad-1 to ad-2
C:\Users\Administrator.RECTOVERSO>ntdsutil
ntdsutil: roles
fsmo maintenance: connections
server connections: connect to server ad-2
Binding to ad-2 ...
Connected to ad-2 using credentials of locally logged on user.
server connections: quit
fsmo maintenance: seize rid master      ---> enter, then will prompt pop up confirmation and select option yes
Attempting safe transfer of RID FSMO before seizure.
FSMO transferred successfully - seizure not required.
Server "ad-2" knows about 5 roles
Schema - CN=NTDS Settings,CN=AD-1,CN=Servers,CN=Default-First-Site-Name,CN=Sites
,CN=Configuration,DC=rectoverso,DC=com
Naming Master - CN=NTDS Settings,CN=AD-1,CN=Servers,CN=Default-First-Site-Name,C
N=Sites,CN=Configuration,DC=rectoverso,DC=com
PDC - CN=NTDS Settings,CN=AD-1,CN=Servers,CN=Default-First-Site-Name,CN=Sites,CN
=Configuration,DC=rectoverso,DC=com
RID - CN=NTDS Settings,CN=AD-2,CN=Servers,CN=Default-First-Site-Name,CN=Sites,CN
=Configuration,DC=rectoverso,DC=com
Infrastructure - CN=NTDS Settings,CN=AD-1,CN=Servers,CN=Default-First-Site-Name,
CN=Sites,CN=Configuration,DC=rectoverso,DC=com
fsmo maintenance: quit
ntdsutil: quit

- okay, to verify that role is moved. Type "netdom query fsmo" without quotes -- the rid master is moved to ad-2
C:\Users\Administrator.RECTOVERSO>netdom query fsmo
Schema master               ad-1.rectoverso.com
Domain naming master        ad-1.rectoverso.com
PDC                         ad-1.rectoverso.com
RID pool manager            ad-2.rectoverso.com
Infrastructure master       ad-1.rectoverso.com
The command completed successfully.




